				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-614879/scp-1256#post-2581645</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 31 Aug 2016 14:42:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Liberonscien</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2280149</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;SCP-1256-1 will attempt to care for the insects to the exclusion of all other activities. This appears to be both to the detriment of SCP-1256-1 and the insects; the attempts of SCP-1256-1 to collect food, repair the hive, and assist in the reproductive cycle of the queen specimens typically result in the expiration of multiple insects and is met with hostility.&quot;</p> <p>The fact that the SCP-1256-1 instances are not good at what they do made me like this scip.<br /> I feel that if they were, I wouldn't like it as much.<br /> I shall upvote this.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
