					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I don't know if what's up now is the original or revised versions, but please keep it as it stands.</p> <p>It reads like one of the incredi-bad self-published works available on Amazon or in most e-reader stores. Y'know, the ones with titles like &quot;Jesus! is the saving of world!&quot; or &quot;Auto-Hydrotherapy: The secrets of immortality hidden in your own urine&quot; and author bios that mention they are acredited (insert some inanity here)-ologists from an institue that almost certainly never existed beyond a website.</p> <p>What I'm saying is that the current excerpt is closer to real life insanity than anything else on the wiki that I can recall at the moment.</p> 
				 	]]>
